  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nIn https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/pull/3252, `func_attrs_with_params_multiline` was replaced with `multiline_func_header`, which is great. I like `multiline_func_header` a lot.\r\n\r\nThere is nothing equivalent for events. I would like my event to be formatted like this:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nevent SetComptroller(\r\n    address indexed owner,\r\n    ISablierV2Comptroller oldComptroller,\r\n    ISablierV2Comptroller newComptroller\r\n);\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut `forge fmt` re-formats it like this:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nevent SetComptroller(\r\n    address indexed owner, ISablierV2Comptroller oldComptroller, ISablierV2Comptroller newComptroller\r\n);\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhereas I would prefer to stick to the same multiline format everywhere (I have set `multiline_func_header` to `all` in my Foundry config).\n\n### Additional context\n\nThis is my `[fmt]` configuration:\r\n\r\n```toml\r\n[fmt]\r\nbracket_spacing = true\r\nint_types = \"long\"\r\nline_length = 120\r\nmultiline_func_header = \"all\"\r\nnumber_underscore = \"thousands\"\r\nquote_style = \"double\"\r\ntab_width = 4\r\nvariable_override_spacing = false\r\nwrap_comments = true\r\n```",
